article.headline: Akron 62, Cleveland St. 50
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Dru Joyce scored 12 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help lead Akron to a 62-50 win over Cleveland State on Monday. The Zips have won six straight. Romeo Travis and Nate Linhart also added 12 points for Akron (11-3), which led by as much as 16 points, 47-31, with 10 minutes left. Cleveland State (6-9), coming off back-to-back wins last week over Detroit and Youngstown State, pulled within eight points when Ije Nwankwo made a free throw with 5:55 left, making it 49-41. But Linhart scored six of his 12 points during Akron's 13-9 run to end the game. The Zips finished shooting 22-of-53 (41.5 percent). Nwankwo led Cleveland State with 15 points, the team's only player in double figures. The Vikings shot 19-of-57 (33.3 percent).
